OL,3,CHome Bargains pledges 'remarkable'
OL,4,C#2.5m to Zoe's Place campaign
OL,6,FLocal MP Ian Byrne described the
OL,7,Fdonation as "unbelievable news" and an
OL,8,F"example of Liverpool coming together."
OL,10,FHe said: "A huge thanks to Home
OL,11,FBargains for their generosity in
OL,12,Fhelping us to take a huge step forward
OL,13,Fto secure a bright future for Zoe's
OL,14,FPlace Liverpool."
OL,16,FZoe's Place has supported children and
OL,17,Ffamilies for over 29 years, ensuring
OL,18,Fthey can live life to the fullest,
OL,19,Fdespite any life-limiting or life-
OL,20,Fthreatening condition or disability
OL,21,Fthey may have.
